OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FChariots of Fire director  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FHugh Hudson dies at 86     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Chariots of Fire director Hugh Hudson  
OL,6, has died aged 86 following a short     
OL,7, illness.                               
OL,9,FHis family said in a statement the     
OL,10,F"beloved husband and father", died at  
OL,11,FCharing Cross Hospital in London on    
OL,12,FFriday.                                
OL,14,FHe is survived by his wife Maryam, his 
OL,15,Fson Thomas and his first wife Sue.     
OL,17,FActor Nigel Havers, who starred in the 
OL,18,F1981 film about the story of two       
OL,19,FBritish runners in the 1920s, said he  
OL,20,Fwas "beyond devastated" by his death.  
